Lightly grease the inside of a microwave-proof mug with the sunflower oil.Put the flour, sugar, remaining oil, milk and mixed spice in the mug. Mix well with a spoon then stir in the pineapple chunks.Microwave on high for 2 minutes, or until well risen. Leave to stand for 2 minutes.Run a knife around the edge of the cake and place a small plate on top of the mug. Invert the cake onto the plate. Sprinkle with sifted icing sugar and serve.